# ==============================================================================
#  HTTP QUERY demo — the on-camera script (bulk price lookup story)
#
#  Story:  You're building an admin dashboard for a wholesaler. The ops team
#          pastes in a list of SKUs (product IDs) to get current prices for
#          their morning report.
#
#  Chapters:
#    1  GET   — works for small lists, breaks on the big morning report
#    2  POST  — moves the list into a body; works, but semantically wrong
#    3  QUERY — same body as POST, but with the right semantics (RFC 10008)
#
#  Open this file in VS Code (with the "REST Client" extension) or JetBrains
#  Rider — each request has a "Send Request" link above it.
#
#  Run the API first:
#      cd src/HttpQuery.Api
#      dotnet run
# ==============================================================================

@host = http://localhost:5080


# ==============================================================================
# CHAPTER 1  —  The GET era
# ==============================================================================

### 1a) Small lookup — 5 SKUs. Clean URL. Fast. Cacheable. Everyone's happy.
GET {{host}}/api/v1/products/prices?ids=1&ids=2&ids=3&ids=4&ids=5
Accept: application/json


### 1b) Medium lookup — 50 SKUs. The URL is getting noticeably long, but
###     still works. This is where you might start feeling nervous.
GET {{host}}/api/v1/products/prices?ids=1000&ids=1001&ids=1002&ids=1003&ids=1004&ids=1005&ids=1006&ids=1007&ids=1008&ids=1009&ids=1010&ids=1011&ids=1012&ids=1013&ids=1014&ids=1015&ids=1016&ids=1017&ids=1018&ids=1019&ids=1020&ids=1021&ids=1022&ids=1023&ids=1024&ids=1025&ids=1026&ids=1027&ids=1028&ids=1029&ids=1030&ids=1031&ids=1032&ids=1033&ids=1034&ids=1035&ids=1036&ids=1037&ids=1038&ids=1039&ids=1040&ids=1041&ids=1042&ids=1043&ids=1044&ids=1045&ids=1046&ids=1047&ids=1048&ids=1049
Accept: application/json


### 1c) THE MORNING REPORT — 1,000 SKUs. This is a real ops workflow: the
###     team pastes in the day's full lookup and expects a response.
###     Kestrel's request line blows past 8 KB and rejects the request
###     BEFORE our controller ever runs. Expected result: 414 URI Too Long.
GET {{host}}/api/v1/products/prices?ids=1000&ids=1001&ids=1002&ids=1003&ids=1004&ids=1005&ids=1006&ids=1007&ids=1008&ids=1009&ids=1010&ids=1011&ids=1012&ids=1013&ids=1014&ids=1015&ids=1016&ids=1017&ids=1018&ids=1019&ids=1020&ids=1021&ids=1022&ids=1023&ids=1024&ids=1025&ids=1026&ids=1027&ids=1028&ids=1029&ids=1030&ids=1031&ids=1032&ids=1033&ids=1034&ids=1035&ids=1036&ids=1037&ids=1038&ids=1039&ids=1040&ids=1041&ids=1042&ids=1043&ids=1044&ids=1045&ids=1046&ids=1047&ids=1048&ids=1049&ids=1050&ids=1051&ids=1052&ids=1053&ids=1054&ids=1055&ids=1056&ids=1057&ids=1058&ids=1059&ids=1060&ids=1061&ids=1062&ids=1063&ids=1064&ids=1065&ids=1066&ids=1067&ids=1068&ids=1069&ids=1070&ids=1071&ids=1072&ids=1073&ids=1074&ids=1075&ids=1076&ids=1077&ids=1078&ids=1079&ids=1080&ids=1081&ids=1082&ids=1083&ids=1084&ids=1085&ids=1086&ids=1087&ids=1088&ids=1089&ids=1090&ids=1091&ids=1092&ids=1093&ids=1094&ids=1095&ids=1096&ids=1097&ids=1098&ids=1099&ids=1100&ids=1101&ids=1102&ids=1103&ids=1104&ids=1105&ids=1106&ids=1107&ids=1108&ids=1109&ids=1110&ids=1111&ids=1112&ids=1113&ids=1114&ids=1115&ids=1116&ids=1117&ids=1118&ids=1119&ids=1120&ids=1121&ids=1122&ids=1123&ids=1124&ids=1125&ids=1126&ids=1127&ids=1128&ids=1129&ids=1130&ids=1131&ids=1132&ids=1133&ids=1134&ids=1135&ids=1136&ids=1137&ids=1138&ids=1139&ids=1140&ids=1141&ids=1142&ids=1143&ids=1144&ids=1145&ids=1146&ids=1147&ids=1148&ids=1149&ids=1150&ids=1151&ids=1152&ids=1153&ids=1154&ids=1155&ids=1156&ids=1157&ids=1158&ids=1159&ids=1160&ids=1161&ids=1162&ids=1163&ids=1164&ids=1165&ids=1166&ids=1167&ids=1168&ids=1169&ids=1170&ids=1171&ids=1172&ids=1173&ids=1174&ids=1175&ids=1176&ids=1177&ids=1178&ids=1179&ids=1180&ids=1181&ids=1182&ids=1183&ids=1184&ids=1185&ids=1186&ids=1187&ids=1188&ids=1189&ids=1190&ids=1191&ids=1192&ids=1193&ids=1194&ids=1195&ids=1196&ids=1197&ids=1198&ids=1199&ids=1200&ids=1201&ids=1202&ids=1203&ids=1204&ids=1205&ids=1206&ids=1207&ids=1208&ids=1209&ids=1210&ids=1211&ids=1212&ids=1213&ids=1214&ids=1215&ids=1216&ids=1217&id