# ==============================================================================
# APPENDIX — the "complex filter" story (bonus if you have video time)
#
# The endpoints below solve a different pain point: rich filter objects with
# nested arrays that GET can't express cleanly at all. QUERY carries the
# whole filter in a body while keeping GET-like semantics.
# ==============================================================================

### GET with a flattened filter — works, but nested/OR-logic can't be expressed.
GET {{host}}/api/v1/products?category=books&minPrice=15&maxPrice=30&tags=scifi&authors=asimov&authors=herbert&authors=leguin&sort=-price&page=1&pageSize=10
Accept: application/json


### POST with the filter as a body.
POST {{host}}/api/v2/products/search
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "category":  "books",
    "minPrice":  15,
    "maxPrice":  30,
    "tags":      ["scifi"],
    "authors":   ["asimov", "herbert", "leguin"],
    "sort":      "-price",
    "page":      1,
    "pageSize":  10
}


### QUERY with the same filter — safe + idempotent + cacheable.
QUERY {{host}}/api/v3/products/search
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "category":  "books",
    "minPrice":  15,
    "maxPrice":  30,
    "tags":      ["scifi"],
    "authors":   ["asimov", "herbert", "leguin"],
    "sort":      "-price",
    "page":      1,
    "pageSize":  10
}

